Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.54,0:00:12.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go out the rear entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.43,0:00:17.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.31,0:00:19.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Saber?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.84,0:00:25.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised to see Saber with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.76,0:00:28.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.94,0:02:08.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer! What's with you finally showing up now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.53,0:02:10.91,Title,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(305,530)}#09  The Distance Between Them
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.53,0:02:12.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious? I sensed a threat to \Nmy Master and rushed to her side.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.37,0:02:14.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it appears I was too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.00,0:02:17.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's all over!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.37,0:02:20.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll fill you in on everything that happened
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.04,0:02:22.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,while you took your sweet time, \Nso you just stand there and listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.88,0:02:27.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I arrived at the worst possible time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.01,0:02:29.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can say that again!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.01,0:02:32.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One Servant was knocked out of the running, \Nand now you decide to show up?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.56,0:02:35.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.23,0:02:37.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, I'll rush to your side at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.06,0:02:41.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, which Servant was eliminated?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.34,0:02:47.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was the Rider-class Servant that disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.07,0:02:51.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know exactly what happened, \Nbut she was probably taken out by Caster.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.66,0:02:53.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.20,0:02:56.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then she really was all talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.83,0:03:00.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, Rider died protecting her Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.08,0:03:02.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are in no position to call her a coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.42,0:03:04.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A coward is a coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.38,0:03:08.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One who calls herself a hero should at least \Ntry to take her opponent out with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.30,0:03:13.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That she was defeated without resistance \Nsuggests she was unable to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.97,0:03:17.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You insult the manner of her death, \Nand you call yourself a hero?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.60,0:03:24.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hero or not, anyone not suited to fight \Nthis battle should disappear early on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.30,0:03:25.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well said.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.65,0:03:28.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, do you wish to fight me, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.28,0:03:33.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am compelled by Command Seal not to fight you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.53,0:03:38.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we were to fight now, I would die just like Rider.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.04,0:03:40.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that in keeping with your code of chivalry, Saber?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.96,0:03:44.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.92,0:03:50.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My alliance with Emiya-kun is only until we \Ndefeat the Master hiding in the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.18,0:03:54.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or what? Do you want to force me to \Nuse another Command Seal on you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.51,0:03:55.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.93,0:04:00.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saber is so noble and righteous, \NI got carried away teasing her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.94,0:04:02.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.90,0:04:06.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, my behavior was immature, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.57,0:04:10.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Out of respect for Rin, I shall overlook your words.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.53,0:04:16.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, if we're going to defeat Caster, the first \Nthing we need to do is locate her Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.28,0:04:21.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fortunately or not, Caster's Master\Ncomes to this school every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.12,0:04:26.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than spooking them and putting \Nthem on guard, we should let them be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.13,0:04:27.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.17,0:04:32.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,after we identify the Master, we attack before \Nthey can return to Ryuudou Temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.05,0:04:33.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.30,0:04:38.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But after a big ruckus like this, won't they stop \Ncoming to school because it's too risky?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.06,0:04:40.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's unlikely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.81,0:04:44.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt Caster's Master still \Npossesses their free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.23,0:04:45.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's her style.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.86,0:04:49.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Her very first move was probably \Nto turn her Master into a puppet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.82,0:04:52.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.03,0:04:56.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, we'll continue our investigation of the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.91,0:05:00.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When we locate Caster's Master, we strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.20,0:05:04.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, that's a reasonable course of action, \Nbut how do we look for them?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.33,0:05:06.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's our homework for next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.54,0:05:08.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're all tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.13,0:05:10.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call it a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.05,0:05:11.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I can still—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.44,0:05:18.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey... Tohsaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.18,0:05:21.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you see that Archer is acting strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.18,0:05:24.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After what happened yesterday, \Nwe need to be on the same page.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.02,0:05:27.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I get it! I'll go home. \NI'll do as you say and go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.73,0:05:30.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,See you tomorrow, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.61,0:05:33.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and good work today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.03,0:05:36.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if only a little, I was \Nable to see you as a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.07,0:05:39.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Archer!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.53,0:05:43.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When we get home, we'll get to \Nthe bottom of this screw-up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.50,0:05:48.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, there it is. The uncharacteristic lack \Nof verbal abuse was troubling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.84,0:05:54.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, look here... Am I going to \Nhave to lay down the law?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.22,0:06:00.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You want to sleep in my room?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.22,0:06:02.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.81,0:06:05.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To prevent a repeat of last night's error,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.77,0:06:07.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall sleep in your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.90,0:06:09.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you have no objections?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.73,0:06:11.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I do! Big ones!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.78,0:06:13.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it comes down to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.15,0:06:17.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it's your fault for falling victim to remote \Nhypnosis from such a great distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.36,0:06:21.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot protect you from Caster's magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.70,0:06:24.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so it's natural that I at least stay in the same room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.41,0:06:27.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's a perfectly sound argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.79,0:06:29.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look, tonight—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.79,0:06:32.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.30,0:06:34.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have you sleep nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.26,0:06:38.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good. That's the logical choice for a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.01,0:06:41.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But only nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.50,0:07:01.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, as if I can fall asleep just like that, idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.50,0:07:15.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is the sixth day since the war commenced.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.96,0:07:19.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are the first to make their way here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.89,0:07:25.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you are withdrawing from the war, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.46,0:07:27.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,O-Of course I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.52,0:07:28.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You want me to die?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.69,0:07:34.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Without a Servant, I can't kill anyone, \Nand I'm no longer a Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.61,0:07:37.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm just an ordinary human.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.24,0:07:38.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just a victim in all this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.97,0:07:43.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's unfair to have people coming to \Nkill us, when we can't do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.45,0:07:48.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What? Do you have a problem with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.75,0:07:50.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.37,0:07:53.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are the first to withdraw from this war,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.42,0:07:56.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and to use this church's services \Nsince it was founded.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.59,0:07:58.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will offer you every hospitality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.30,0:08:03.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What? You're saying I'm the only \None that's been knocked out?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.85,0:08:07.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When my grandfather finds out \Nabout this, what will he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.48,0:08:11.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is all you people's fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.06,0:08:13.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You stuck me with that crappy Servant, Rider!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.19,0:08:18.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Then Rider was of no use to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.82,0:08:20.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.07,0:08:25.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all I did for her, she went and died like a dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.41,0:08:28.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Any other Servant would have \Nbeen way more useful!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.50,0:08:33.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, I did exactly as Grandfather said!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.50,0:08:35.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My preparations were perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.59,0:08:38.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But those bastards all got in my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.80,0:08:42.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was two against one! I didn't stand \Na chance with those odds!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.22,0:08:45.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it wasn't my fault that I lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.26,0:08:48.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Their Servants were better than mine, that's all!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.81,0:08:53.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Always looking down on me with \Nthose smug expressions!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.56,0:09:00.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Crap, crap, crap, crap, crap! \NCrap, crap, crap, crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.49,0:09:09.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're saying that you \Nstill have the resolve to fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.16,0:09:14.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are most fortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.00,0:09:18.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There happens to be one available Servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.63,0:09:27.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And what do you think that doctor said to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.43,0:09:30.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"It's rare to see someone so healthy, Fujimura-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.27,0:09:34.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so perhaps you'd care to donate \Nsome blood? Ho ho ho!"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.84,0:09:38.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a patient, too, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.44,0:09:40.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.44,0:09:41.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Refill!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.69,0:09:46.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, isn't it great news that most \Nhad nothing worse than anemia?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.57,0:09:48.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't have to close the school, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.08,0:09:50.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.15,0:09:53.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad that classes will be held as usual, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.91,0:09:55.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's a little strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.04,0:09:57.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Strange how?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.54,0:09:59.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it was such a huge mess,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.63,0:10:03.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,they have no idea what really caused it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.34,0:10:08.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Something about chemicals in an empty \Nclassroom on the first floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.09,0:10:11.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They spent all night scouring the \Nbuilding from top to bottom,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.89,0:10:14.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and that's all they have.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.10,0:10:17.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But the students in the hospital will \Nbe able to go home soon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.15,0:10:23.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It'll differ from person to person, \Nbut most will be able to go home today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.65,0:10:25.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, including Sakura-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.90,0:10:26.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.24,0:10:30.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you have time, you should \Nstop by and see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.37,0:10:33.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I bet Sakura-chan will be happy to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.17,0:10:42.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,T-Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.05,0:10:45.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's definitely something \Nsuspicious about Issei.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.76,0:10:50.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Suspicious? How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.30,0:10:52.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Caster's Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.85,0:10:57.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Caster's made Ryuudou Temple her base, \Nand Issei comes to school from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.52,0:10:59.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those things can't be unrelated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.02,0:11:02.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, it could be a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.82,0:11:06.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What? You're sticking up for Issei, Emiya-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.03,0:11:08.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.70,0:11:12.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.79,0:11:15.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.08,0:11:16.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.38,0:11:25.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I get it... I get what you're trying to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.13,0:11:27.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I get it, so don't give me that look.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.42,0:11:30.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how to handle it when you sulk on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.80,0:11:32.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sulking!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.43,0:11:38.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I can't imagine Issei working with \NCaster to do something so horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.80,0:11:41.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have you forgotten what Archer said yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.65,0:11:45.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His theory that Caster's controlling her Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.11,0:11:49.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, isn't it possible that Issei \Ncan't remember that he's a Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.99,0:11:52.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That makes sense, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.90,0:11:55.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What? Do you have another theory?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.74,0:11:56.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.62,0:12:00.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good! I'll check him out, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.58,0:12:03.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fine! I'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.25,0:12:04.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll look into him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.71,0:12:06.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave Issei to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.96,0:12:10.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll find out whether or not he's a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.26,0:12:14.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Trust me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.55,0:12:19.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't hold back just because Issei's \Na friend, and I wouldn't lie to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.02,0:12:21.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.60,0:12:25.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inform me the instant you know \None way or the other. Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.48,0:12:27.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.99,0:12:32.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, how do you plan to assess him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.99,0:12:35.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.45,0:12:44.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't going to do your usual thing and\Nask, "Hey, Issei, are you a Master?" right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.82,0:12:49.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry! There are ways to find out \Nif someone's a Master without asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.05,0:12:53.55,Next,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Student Council Office
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.93,0:12:55.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.89,0:13:03.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Issei...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.11,0:13:05.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask questions. Just take off your clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.82,0:13:09.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.82,0:13:15.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.24,0:13:19.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this some new form of interrogation? \NAre you gonna question me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.61,0:13:22.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. And you'll answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.87,0:13:23.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look, just strip.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.50,0:13:29.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop this, fool! And you call yourself \Nthe son of a warrior family?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.13,0:13:27.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up and strip!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.35,0:13:42.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What a relief. It's a real relief!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.35,0:13:44.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's a relief?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.19,0:13:48.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the meaning of this, \Nmaking me do that for nothing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.36,0:13:49.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.48,0:13:50.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Issei.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.98,0:13:53.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you think that what you did was wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.07,0:13:56.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I insist that you explain your reasons!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.24,0:13:59.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I can't give you the details,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.87,0:14:02.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but I had to find out something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.45,0:14:04.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I know, we're all good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.96,0:14:13.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Issei...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.42,0:14:16.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have you noticed anything \Nstrange at the temple recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.59,0:14:18.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.18,0:14:22.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you think of anything that \Nisn't like it used to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.87,0:14:24.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing in particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.43,0:14:26.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The mountain is the picture of tranquility!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.85,0:14:28.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Issei...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.94,0:14:35.90,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,School has now ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.66,0:14:40.40,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Students are not permitted to remain \Non campus after school hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.03,0:14:43.87,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please leave immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.19,0:14:46.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She went home?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.50,0:14:49.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Tohsaka-san left a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.21,0:14:54.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell? She said to \Nreport to her right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.82,0:15:22.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.58,0:15:32.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tohsaka, what are you doing here—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.59,0:15:36.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,T-T-Tohsaka, w-w-wai—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.17,0:15:39.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Be quiet. If you cause a scene, he'll spot us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.34,0:15:41.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who'll spot us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.64,0:15:44.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Move. Go in further.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.56,0:15:47.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Boobs... Tohsaka, your—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.56,0:15:48.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I said to keep quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.98,0:15:50.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There. In front of Sakura's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.06,0:15:53.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,See that weird guy standing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.86,0:15:58.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Blond hair...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.36,0:15:59.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A foreigner?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.70,0:16:02.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right. He's been watching the \NMatou house for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.34,0:16:04.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.84,0:16:23.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if he's the guy who \Nwas talking to Sakura earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.22,0:16:24.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To Sakura?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.14,0:16:28.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it seemed like he was \Nasking Sakura for directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.31,0:16:34.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you doing here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.36,0:16:36.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I could ask you the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.99,0:16:42.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's with the evil grin?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.61,0:16:44.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.20,0:16:47.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that makes sense. \NInstead of looking for other Masters,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.37,0:16:51.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you're more concerned about the underclassman \Nwho always comes over to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.42,0:16:55.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think I understand you a little \Nbetter now, Emiya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.50,0:16:57.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.13,0:17:01.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I came to report to you \Nabout Issei, you'd already left.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.47,0:17:05.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Issei's in the clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.55,0:17:08.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What? You already checked him out, Emiya-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.52,0:17:11.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I did. Issei isn't a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.52,0:17:14.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't believe me, I don't really care.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.19,0:17:17.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I believe you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.77,0:17:20.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't the kind to lie, Emiya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.57,0:17:23.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you say Issei is innocent, he's innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.12,0:17:28.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But how did you find out?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.91,0:17:31.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Obviously, I made him take his clothes off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.87,0:17:35.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I took off his top and checked \Nif he had any Command Seals.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.59,0:17:40.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka, why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.92,0:17:44.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried about Sakura, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.97,0:17:47.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we're just acquaintances.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.60,0:17:50.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,According to what Fuji-nee said, \Nshe'll be discharged today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.68,0:17:52.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She might be at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.69,0:17:55.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.65,0:17:59.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka? You're leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.41,0:18:12.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I want to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.20,0:18:14.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.12,0:18:18.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um, hypothetically...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.38,0:18:21.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How do you think someone \Nwould feel growing up
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.59,0:18:27.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,if she'd been given away for adoption to another \Nfamily, without any say in the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.37,0:18:31.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.77,0:18:34.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She wouldn't feel one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.19,0:18:38.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If her new home is nice, she wouldn't complain,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.73,0:18:41.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and if it's not so nice, she would, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.36,0:18:45.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see... I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.15,0:18:48.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I even asking such an obvious question?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.74,0:18:55.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's brainstorm ways to find \NCaster at school tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.25,0:18:57.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.59,0:19:08.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.68,0:19:14.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while since you practiced \Nkendo in the old dojo, Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.56,0:19:16.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A while?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.89,0:19:19.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even though he had a fine sparring \Npartner like you, Taiga?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.11,0:19:22.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose it has been...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.23,0:19:24.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After Dad died, I guess I stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.07,0:19:26.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.32,0:19:30.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When Kiritsugu-san died, Shirou suddenly \Nstopped picking up his bamboo sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.41,0:19:33.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It made me so sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.54,0:19:36.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fuji-nee, don't bring up the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.83,0:19:38.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.21,0:19:41.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, tales from Shirou's childhood?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.17,0:19:43.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, want to hear? Want to hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.75,0:19:45.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I am curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.13,0:19:50.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Prepare to be regaled by big sister Taiga!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.72,0:19:54.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was adorable as a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.43,0:20:00.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was so trusting of everyone, \Nand he'd instantly agree to any request.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.02,0:20:03.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But he had a strange stubborn streak.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.77,0:20:07.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once he set his mind to something, \Nhe wouldn't budge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.40,0:20:10.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he was the polar opposite \Nof Kiritsugu-san in that regard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.11,0:20:12.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Polar opposite?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.12,0:20:16.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kiritsugu-san was the kind of guy \Nwho was accepting of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.41,0:20:21.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He thought good and bad were subjective. \NA "what will be, will be" kind of guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.62,0:20:25.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, if he saw someone \Nin need, he'd try to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.71,0:20:29.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And Shirou would always try \Nto mimic Kiritsugu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.47,0:20:33.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou saw things in black and white \Nmore than Kiritsugu-san did.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.09,0:20:38.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He'd go around and beat up the town bullies, \Nsaying, "It's wrong to do bad things!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.68,0:20:42.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yep, even back then, Shirou was \Nalready a hero of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.90,0:20:46.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you want to be a hero of justice?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.90,0:20:49.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's hard to answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.32,0:20:52.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because I look up to them, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.03,0:20:53.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You look up to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.62,0:20:55.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To heroes of justice?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.78,0:20:58.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.33,0:21:00.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.71,0:21:03.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.84,0:21:04.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.96,0:21:07.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I'm going to my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.77,0:21:22.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why? What am I afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.85,0:21:25.44,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you want to be a hero of justice?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.02,0:21:30.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My reason for being a hero of justice...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.89,0:21:31.65,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.65,0:21:34.78,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Since you can't, I'll become one for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.53,0:21:39.29,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to follow in his footsteps.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.29,0:21:42.29,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't any such thing in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.08,0:21:44.78,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let your ideals drag you to your death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.54,0:21:46.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Screw you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.96,0:21:49.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How can you know unless you try?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.81,0:23:27.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We attack tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.31,0:23:29.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He won't live to see the end of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.48,0:23:32.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They are nothing more than living sacrifices.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.19,0:23:35.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A weapon... I need a weapon that will let me fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.15,0:23:37.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Such an irritating boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.03,0:23:40.03,Next,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(470,1)}Next time \NThe Fifth Contractor
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.11,0:23:39.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe I shall kill you.
